# Frontend Conventions

## Stack (Locked 2026-05-07)

- React 19 + Vite + TypeScript (strict).
- Tailwind CSS **v4** with **CSS variable tokens** (no raw hex outside the token layer).
- shadcn/ui (latest) for primitives. Always prefer composing a shadcn primitive over building from scratch.
- TanStack Query for **all** server state.
- Recharts for charts.
- pnpm-managed workspace.

## Path Alias

- Always import via `@/*` for anything inside `frontend/src/`.
- Never use long relative chains (`../../../`).

## Theming

- Class-based dark mode is wired into the architecture (`<html class="dark">`).
- **Default and only UI-exposed mode is light** for now. Don't surface a theme toggle until explicitly asked.
- All colors come from CSS variable tokens. If you find yourself writing `#fff` or `bg-white` in a component, stop — define or reuse a token.

## Feature-Sliced Layout

```
frontend/src/
├── features/<feature>/   # vertical slices: upload, results, fairness, auth
├── components/ui/        # shadcn primitives (generated)
├── components/<shared>/  # shared composite components
├── lib/                  # api client, query keys, helpers
├── hooks/                # cross-feature hooks
└── routes/               # route definitions
```

A feature folder owns its own components, hooks, types, and tests.

## Server State

- Every server fetch goes through TanStack Query.
- Define **query keys as constants** in `lib/queryKeys.ts`. Don't inline strings.
- Mutations: invalidate the precise affected key, not the entire cache.

## Forms & Validation

- React Hook Form + Zod resolver.
- Reuse Zod schemas from `@shared/*` whenever the same shape exists on the backend.

## Accessibility

- Use semantic HTML (`<button>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`).
- All interactive elements are keyboard-reachable and have visible focus states.
- shadcn primitives bring a11y by default — don't strip it out.

## Performance

- No unnecessary `useMemo` / `useCallback` — only when profiling shows a need or when stabilizing a dep.
- Code-split routes via `React.lazy` for large pages.
- Charts: pass memoized data, not recomputed-on-every-render arrays.

## Lint / Format

- Strict ESLint + Prettier scripts must pass before any commit.
- Husky pre-commit runs lint + format.

## Tests

- Vitest + Testing Library.
- Test the user-visible behavior, not the implementation.
- Mock the **network**, not the components.
